<i>No, it's a documentary, I guess.</i>

15
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:47,859
<i>You can't tell until the film's made.</i>

16
00:01:47,860 --> 00:01:50,499
<i>Excuse us, we have to start shooting.</i>

17
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:53,779
Excuse me, Sir, what is this film?

18
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:56,339
<i>It's about homework.
What school do you go to?</i>

19
00:01:56,340 --> 00:01:58,819
Shahid Massoumi.

20
00:02:00,020 --> 00:02:03,039
<i>It's about homework...
Have you done yours?</i>

21
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,418
Yes.

22
00:02:04,419 --> 00:02:06,379
My homework's better than theirs.

23
00:02:06,380 --> 00:02:08,219
<i>Off you go to school then.</i>

24
00:02:08,220 --> 00:02:12,059
Goodbye, Sir.
- Salaam.

25
00:02:12,060 --> 00:02:13,719
<i>Excuse me, Sir.</i>

26
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:18,479
<i>I'm interested in films and I'm
familiar with your work, Mr. Kiarostami.</i>

27
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:19,679
<i>Thank you.</i>

28
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:23,159
<i>I've seen one of your films too,
on TV.</i>

29
00:02:23,160 --> 00:02:25,679
<i>it was filmed at school... in class.</i>

30
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,079
<i>'The First Graders'?</i>

31
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:29,318
<i>Is it on the same theme?</i>

32
00:02:29,319 --> 00:02:34,679
<i>Well, the theme isn't clear yet
because I don't work from a script.</i>

33
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:38,319
<i>It's based on impressions...
I've only started today.</i>

34
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:41,199
<i>To tell you the truth,
I came across a problem...</i>

35
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:44,919
<i>when I was helping my own child
with his homework.</i>

36
00:02:45,860 --> 00:02:51,299
<i>Homework's supposed to be for kids
but adults are even more involved.</i>

37
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:57,339
<i>So I tought I'd bring a camera over
and see what's happening here.</i>

38
00:02:57,340 --> 00:03:01,419
<i>See if it's only my child's problem,
my own problem...</i>

39
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:05,899
<i>or the educational system's.</i>

40
00:03:06,580 --> 00:03:11,659
<i>So we'll be observing other parents
and children and hearing their views.</i>

41
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:14,379
<i>In fact, to give you the right
answer...</i>

42
00:03:14,380 --> 00:03:17,899
<i>I'd say it's not a movie
in the usual sense.</i>

43
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:21,499
<i>It's a research project.</i>

44
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:25,859
<i>You could say it's a visual study
of pupils homework assignments.</i>

45
00:03:25,860 --> 00:03:28,139
<i>Well, good luck to you.</i>

